# SciJudge — Science Fair Congress Judging System

## What this app is
A multi-role web app for managing science fair events. Admins create events, set up categories/criteria, and manage judges. Teachers submit projects on behalf of their schools (no login). Judges log in and score assigned projects via sliders. One codebase, one deployment, one URL — no separate apps.

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 App Router (NEVER use Pages Router)
- Language: TypeScript (strict)
- Database: PostgreSQL via Neon (serverless)
- ORM: Prisma (NEVER write raw SQL)
- Auth: Clerk (multi-role: ADMIN + JUDGE)
- File Uploads: UploadThing
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Email: Resend
- Charts: Recharts
- AI: Vercel AI Gateway + AI SDK (anthropic/claude-opus-4-6 by default, claude-sonnet-4-6 for fast/cheap tasks)
- Deployment: Vercel

